Spiral Staircase is British folk musician Ralph McTell's second album. Produced by
Gus Dudgeon and released in the UK in 1969, its opening track, "Streets of London",
has become McTell's signature tune.

The UK 2007 CD release includes four bonus tracks that were re-mixed or re-recorded
in 1970 for "Revisited"
